üõ†Ô∏è Step-by-Step Solution for Day 17: Create IAM Group (iamgroup_mark)
Follow these exact steps in order:

Login to the AWS Console

Open a web browser.

Go to the provided Console URL: https://345865620496.signin.aws.amazon.com/console?region=us-east-1

Enter the provided credentials:

Username: kk_labs_user_982604

Password: Vpkh!p71M5%@

Click Sign In.

Navigate to the IAM Service

Once logged in, at the top search bar type "IAM" and click on the "IAM" service.

Go to the User Groups Page

In the left-hand navigation menu, find and click on "User groups" (under "Access management").

Start Creating the New Group

On the User groups page, click the "Create group" button.

Step 1: Specify Group Details

In the "User group name" box, type exactly: iamgroup_mark.

IMPORTANT FOR THIS LAB: Do not add any users to this group yet. The list of users will be empty.

Click the blue "Next" button at the bottom.

Step 2: Attach Permissions Policies (Skip This Step)

On the "Attach permissions policies" page, you will not attach any policies for this task.

Simply click the blue "Next" button again.

Step 3: Review and Create

You will see a review page. Double-check that the "User group name" is iamgroup_mark and that no policies are attached.

Scroll to the bottom and click the orange "Create group" button.

Verification (Final Step)

You will see a green success banner saying "The user group iamgroup_mark was created successfully."

You will be taken back to the list of all user groups. Verify that iamgroup_mark appears in the list.

Task Complete! ‚úÖ You have successfully created the IAM group iamgroup_mark.

